TDD exercise complete. All 9 tests passing across the full Game of Life implementation:

**Tests implemented (Red-Green-Refactor cycle):**
1. Empty grid returns empty grid
2. Single live cell dies (underpopulation)
3. Two adjacent cells die (underpopulation)
4. Cell with 2 neighbors survives
5. Cell with 3 neighbors survives
6. Cell with 4 neighbors dies (overpopulation)
7. Dead cell with 3 neighbors becomes alive (reproduction)
8. Block pattern stays unchanged (still life)
9. Blinker oscillates to alternate form

**Implementation highlights:**
- Sparse representation using `[x, y]` coordinate pairs
- `cellKey` — converts coordinates to string for Set lookups
- `isNeighbor` — checks if two cells are adjacent
- `countLiveNeighbors` — counts live neighbors of a cell
- `getDeadNeighbors` — finds all unique dead cells adjacent to any live cell
- `nextGeneration` — combines survivors (2-3 neighbors) with births (dead cells with exactly 3 neighbors)
